extended fingers of the fallen man as he threw
them up, and crushing and crunching deeply into
the scull. The unhappy woodman sank back,
without groan or further word, even as an ox
beneath
the stunning stroke of the butcher.
CHAPTER V.
A rash and ruinous deed. Thou art too quick;
Thy madness blinds thee, and thy rude stroke falls
Wide of the victim.
There
